{Speech 2}{}{What's the matter?}
{Speech 2 Answer Exit}{}{Sorry, my mistake. I'm leaving now. [Exit]}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{I have some questions. Could you help?}
{Speech 3}{}{Go ahead and ask.}
{Speech 3 Answer 4}{}{Who are you and what do you do?}
{Speech 4}{}{Johann Hartmann. Captain Johann Hartmann. Commander of the City Guard. Any more questions?}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{Commander of the Guard? Wow! Can I become a guardsman? All my life I @sex@|dreamed|dreamed| of a military career. Romance, military camaraderie, protecting the civilian population. Wonderful.}
{Speech 4 Answer 6}{}{Commander of the Guard? Wow! Can I become a guardsman? All my life I @sex@|dreamed|dreamed| of a military career. Romance, military camaraderie, protecting the civilian population. Wonderful.}
{Speech 4 Answer Exit}{}{No, sir! Permission to leave?@@No questions, farewell.}
{Speech 5}{}{No, it won't work. Go bulk up, gain some experience, get yourself into shape… Then we'll talk.}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{But I'm already the best@sex@|||!}
{Speech 6}{}{Romance, protection… Are you right in the head? Did they drop you off the table as a child? Hmm. Well, in principle we are recruiting. Are you @sex@|sure|sure| you want this?}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{Yes, sir. That is exactly my wish!}
{Speech 6 Answer Exit}{}{I need to think it over some more. [Exit]}
{Speech 7}{}{Well then. BUT! Before becoming a guardsman, you must prove that you are @sex@|worthy|worthy| of the rank. And for that you'll have to try hard. Very hard! But afterward - all the perks: passage into the city, free medicine, decent money. What do you say?}
{Speech 7 Answer 8}{}{Sounds great, and difficulties don't scare me.}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{So there's a catch here too. Forget it, I'm fed up.}
{Speech 8}{}{Well then, here's your first task. You need to fight one of our men hand-to-hand. Show what you've got.}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{Why not. I figure it's either a smashed fist or a split skull. Which one's the guy?}
{Speech 8 Answer 10}{}{Well, I, uh, you know. My unarmed combat skills, they, uh, aren't trained up… Maybe we could do it some other way?}
{Speech 9}{}{Now that's the spirit! There's a lad standing off by himself - go duke it out with him.}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{As you say...}
{Speech 10}{}{Oh, mama! A soldier, a guardsman, what can I say. Get out of here, so I don't see you again.}
{Speech 11}{}{All right, first trial - passed. Shall we continue?}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{Always ready!}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{I need time to prepare. [Exit]}
{Speech 12}{}{Now, in service you'll often have to use your personal weapon. Right now your task is to show that you can handle it. Here, take these. [Hands over two rifles fouled until the bolts won't move] By tomorrow I want them shining like new! Forward, march!}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir! [Exit]}
{Speech 13}{}{Well? How's it going?}
{Speech 13 Answer Exit}{}{It's in progress... [Exit]}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{A weapon loves tender care, cleaning and oiling! Here are your gats!}
{Speech 13 Answer 15}{}{I @sex@|thought|thought | about it a bit. And @sex@|decided|decided|  to attach something to them.}
{Speech 14}{}{Excellent!}
{Speech 14 Answer Exit}{}{@sex@|Glad|glad| to serve! [Exit]}
{Speech 15}{}{What's this improvising! Hand it over! What did you… Oh. Not bad, not bad at all. Well done. Hmm. Keep one for yourself. Would you look at that. What advanced recruits we're getting these days, huh…}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{@sex@|Glad|glad| to serve! [Exit]}
{Speech 16}{}{I'm listening.}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{Will there be more tasks, or am I in the Guard already?}
{Speech 17}{}{Of course. Of course there will be, and of course you're not in the Guard yet. Next up is drill training.}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{So what are we waiting for?}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{Oh. I'll be right here, I'm right here… [Exit]}
{Speech 18}{}{Right. Fall into formation next to these mon… guardsmen, and do everything just like them. Got it? Go!}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir! [Exit]}
{Speech 19}{}{Talk later. I've got training going on! Clear the @sex@||| grounds, now!}
{Speech 19 Answer Exit}{}{But what about me...}
{Speech 20}{}{Right. @pname@. There you are.}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Always at your service, Captain.}
{Speech 21}{}{Welll, the trials are over for you. So. Haven't @sex@|changed your mind|changed your mind | about joining the Guard?}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit}{}{I need time to make a decision. [Exit]}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{I don't change my decisions.}
{Speech 22}{}{If your intentions to join the Guard are unchanged, I must administer the oath. Stand at attention and repeat after me: I, @pname@...}
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{I, @pname@...}
{Speech 23}{}{Joining the ranks of the Guardsmen of Vault City…}
{Speech 23 Answer 24}{}{Joining the ranks of the Guardsmen of Vault City…}
{Speech 24}{}{Do take this oath and solemnly swear. To be an honest, loyal, disciplined, vigilant warrior. To bear with dignity the hardships and deprivations of military service…}
{Speech 24 Answer 25}{}{Do take this oath and solemnly swear. To be an honest, loyal, disciplined, vigilant warrior. To bear with dignity the hardships and deprivations of military service…}
{Speech 25}{}{To unquestioningly carry out the orders and commands of commanders and superiors. To spare neither my blood, nor, if need be, my life in defense of the City and the fight against its enemies…}
{Speech 25 Answer 26}{}{To unquestioningly carry out the orders and commands of commanders and superiors. To spare neither my blood, nor, if need be, my life in defense of the City and the fight against its enemies…}
{Speech 26}{}{And if I should break this solemn oath, may I be struck by the punishment of a military tribunal. And may God have mercy on my soul.}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{And if I should break this solemn oath, may I be struck by the punishment of a military tribunal. And may God have mercy on my soul.}
{Speech 27}{}{My congratulations, guardsman. So. Your pay is 68 coins a day. It's credited to your bank account. That's for now. Raise your rank - the pay goes up. You may enter the city without a pass. Once a week the doc in the vault will issue 5 stimpaks. Also once a week - free repairs at Valerie's. You receive service assignments from me personally. Is everything clear? Dismissed.}
{Speech 27 Answer Exit}{}{Servant of the people! [Exit]}
{Speech 28}{}{Right, Private @pname@. Front and center!}
{Speech 28 Answer 29}{}{Private @pname@ reporting as ordered!}
{Speech 29}{}{Listen to my orders. You're being assigned to a patrol. Three of our men will be with you, you'll make the rounds of the city, eliminate all hostile elements. Protect your own men, destroy the enemy. Mind you don't mix them up, Kutuzov. Report back when it's done. What's unclear?}
{Speech 29 Answer 30}{}{Who will command the patrol?}
{Speech 30}{}{Go out the gate to the Guard barracks. Find Corporal Shrimp, you'll be under his command. March!}
{Speech 30 Answer Exit}{}{All clear! Permission to double-time?}
{Speech 30 Answer 71}{}{Permission to ask a question, sir? Why is the corporal called "Shrimp"?}
{Speech 31}{}{Report!}
{Speech 31 Answer 32}{}{Your order has been carried out!}
{Speech 31 Answer 33}{}{Your order has been carried out!}
{Speech 31 Answer 34}{}{Your order has been carried out!}
{Speech 31 Answer 35}{}{I, uh. It didn't work out…}
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{Forgive me, Captain, I'll be back soon.}
{Speech 32}{}{Excellent, Private. Right, rest for two days, then come see me. That's an order. }
{Speech 32 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir.[Exit]}
{Speech 33}{}{Handled it well enough. Not without losses, but still. You can rest now. Come back in two days.}
{Speech 33 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 34}{}{Hmph. I've already heard. I'm ashamed I took you into the Guard… But, for lack of a cook, you make do with the janitor. So, dear janitor, come back in a couple of days. There'll be a chance to redeem yourself.}
{Speech 34 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 35}{}{Right, Private, I don't want to see this again. A week of self-training, then come see me.}
{Speech 35 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir.[Exit]}
{Speech 36}{}{Private @pname@!}
{Speech 36 Answer 37}{}{Here, sir!}
{Speech 37}{}{Allow me to congratulate you on your promotion to the next rank - junior sergeant!}
{Speech 37 Answer 38}{}{Servant of the people!}
{Speech 38}{}{Your pay is increased to 98 coins a day. It'll be transferred to your account. Once a week the doc will issue you a super stimpak. Weapon repair at Valerie's - 1 gun a day. Any questions?}
{Speech 38 Answer 39}{}{No, sir! @sex@|Glad|Glad| to serve!}
{Speech 39}{}{At ease, junior sergeant. Celebrate the promotion with friends, report to me tomorrow.}
{Speech 39 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 40}{}{Junior sergeant @pname@!}
{Speech 40 Answer 41}{}{Here, Captain!}
{Speech 41}{}{I have a task for you.}
{Speech 41 Answer 42}{}{Listening, Captain, sir.}
{Speech 41 Answer Exit}{}{I need to adjust my gear. [Exit]}
{Speech 42}{}{Listen to the briefing. We've received information that mutant gangs are massing in the city's vicinity again. But the information is still unconfirmed. We need to conduct reconnaissance. You'll handle this. The task - scout the surroundings, find the mutants' lair. Pinpoint the location precisely. Report to me. Under no circumstances, I repeat - under no circumstances reveal yourself. No armed clashes. Find it - and report. Is the task clear?}
{Speech 42 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. Permission to carry out? [Exit]}
{Speech 43}{}{Junior sergeant @pname@! Awaiting your report.}
{Speech 43 Answer 44}{}{Yes, sir, Captain! The information is confirmed. It's super mutants. The base has been found. They didn't spot me.}
{Speech 43 Answer 45}{}{The base was found, but… I had to engage them in combat, Captain.}
{Speech 43 Answer Exit}{}{Permission to report, I am in the process of carrying it out, Captain, sir! [Exit]}
{Speech 44}{}{Excellent work, @pname@! I must think over the strategy, come see me tomorrow.}
{Speech 44 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 45}{}{You @sex@|stupid ass|brainless sheep|, junior sergeant! Now they've changed location and we have to search for them all over again. What were you @sex@|listening|listening| with when I gave the task? Out of here. Come back in a week.}
{Speech 45 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 46}{}{Junior sergeant @pname@!}
{Speech 46 Answer 47}{}{Here, Captain!}
{Speech 47}{}{@sex@|Ready|Ready| for the next task?}
{Speech 47 Answer 48}{}{Yes, sir.}
{Speech 47 Answer Exit}{}{I need time to prepare. [Exit]}
{Speech 48}{}{The command entrusts you with an operation to wipe out the mutants' lair. I'm placing five guardsmen under your command. They'll wait for you on site. The objective - reach the super mutant base you discovered and conduct a full sweep. Super mutants are tough fighters, so you must be excellently prepared for the operation. I await your report here when it's done. No questions? Carry on!}
{Speech 48 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir! [Exit]}
{Speech 49}{}{Junior sergeant @pname@! Awaiting your report.}
{Speech 49 Answer Exit}{}{I'm working on it, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 49 Answer 50}{}{Permission to report, the task is complete! }
{Speech 49 Answer 73}{}{Captain, sir. We were too late... The mutants managed to change position...}
{Speech 50}{}{Glad to hear it. Report the details.}
{Speech 50 Answer 51}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. No casualties among our personnel.}
{Speech 50 Answer 52}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. Casualties among our personnel - 1 man.}
{Speech 50 Answer 52*}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. Casualties among our personnel - 2 men.}
{Speech 50 Answer 52**}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. Casualties among our personnel - 3 men.}
{Speech 50 Answer 53}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. Casualties among our personnel - 4 men.}
{Speech 50 Answer 53*}{}{We destroyed 9 super mutants. I lost all of my men. The fight was hard.}
{Speech 51}{}{Excellent work, simply superb. Here, this is from me personally. Stay close by, I'll need you again in three days.}
{Speech 51 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 52}{}{Not bad. And you stayed within the casualty quota. Report to me in three days. For now - rest.}
{Speech 52 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, sir. [Exit]}
{Speech 53}{}{Too high a price for such a task. You don't take care of your men at all. That's not how you become a good commander. I'm displeased. I'll expect you here in three days.}
