{Speech 55}{}{Congratulations on your promotion to the military rank of senior sergeant. Your pay is increased to 151 coins a day. Once a week you'll receive 2 super stimpaks from the doctor in the vault. Weapon repair at Valerie's - 2 items a day.}
{Speech 55 Answer 56}{}{Servant of the people!}
{Speech 56}{}{At ease, senior sergeant. You're free for now. Don't go away from the city for too long. You may be needed.}
{Speech 56 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, Captain! [Exit]}
{Speech 57}{}{Senior sergeant @pname@! Front and center!}
{Speech 57 Answer 58}{}{Here, Captain!}
{Speech 58}{}{I have a task of special importance for you. @sex@|Ready|Ready|?}
{Speech 58 Answer 59}{}{Yes, sir.}
{Speech 58 Answer Exit}{}{I'll come when I'm better prepared. [Exit]}
{Speech 59}{}{Listen to me carefully, @pname@. The mission I'm entrusting to you is very important for the City. And the reward for completing it will be considerable. But in case of failure… I don't want to think about it, but know that if you fail, I can make your life real miserable.}
{Speech 59 Answer 60}{}{No doubt about it… Ahem. I @sex@|meant|meant| to say - I am @sex@|ready|ready| to carry out any task from the command.}
{Speech 59 Answer Exit}{}{Well, if you put it that way, I'd like to ask to be relieved of this task. [Exit]}
{Speech 60}{}{So then. The events of recent weeks lead to certain conclusions. Our analysts don't like the increase in mutant activity. From this follows your task. \n Your mission - travel to the NCR and negotiate with General Sheiman for military aid for our city. Get the point across to him that we're not asking them to get involved in every skirmish on our territory, but want to secure support in case of a serious conflict. In turn, we too will be ready to render them aid. If needed.}
{Speech 60 Answer 61}{}{Understood. It's serious business. Can you advise anything?}
{Speech 61}{}{I can't give you any of our men to help, sorry. I strongly recommend you go to Sheiman not alone, but with three or four friends. Are there people you trust? They should be serious people, no less experienced than you. Let him see that we're not a bunch of schoolkids here.}
{Speech 61 Answer 62}{}{Yes, sir. I'll find the people. Anything else?}
{Speech 62}{}{Well, I can't advise you on how to conduct negotiations. I'm no diplomat. And in general I prefer action over words, so it's all at your discretion.\n}
{Speech 62 Answer 63}{}{Permission to leave?}
{Speech 63}{}{Go. Good luck.}
